`onclick` is a default html attribute to fire custom javascript, which is not allowed in amp.

You have to use the binding syntax of amp, which could look like this (last 4 lines):

```html
&lt;amp-img
  	src=&quot;https://preview.amp.dev/static/samples/img/amp.jpg&quot;
	width=&quot;1080&quot;
	height=&quot;610&quot;
	layout=&quot;responsive&quot;
	alt=&quot;AMP&quot;
	on=&quot;tap:AMP.setState({…})&quot;
    tabindex=&quot;0&quot;
	role=&quot;button&quot;&gt;
&lt;/amp-img&gt;
```

For `onclick=&quot;…&quot;` it is `on=&quot;tap:…&quot;` but there are also many other events you can use. Here is a [list][1].

Don&#39;t forget to set `tabindex` and `role` attributes when you use `tap` events on custom elements. Otherwise you get new validation errors.


  [1]: https://amp.dev/documentation/guides-and-tutorials/learn/amp-actions-and-events/#element-specific-events

